1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
KittaChat is a full-stack realtime communication platform
for direct messages and group collaboration.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
It also supports shared files, presence,
and peer-to-peer audio and video calls.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,000
In direct chat, Alice sees her message immediately
through optimistic UI.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,000
The client preserves a generated idempotency key
across network retries.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,000
MongoDB safely upserts the message
by sender and idempotency key.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Bob receives the persisted message in realtime,
even through another backend replica.

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Delivery stays responsive without claiming
exactly-once semantics.

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:40,000
The sidebar reacts to incoming activity
without a page refresh.

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Sam's message increments unread state
and moves the conversation upward.

10
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Filter-specific cursor pagination keeps
direct and group views independent.

11
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Infinite scroll loads older conversations
without losing the active selection.

12
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Batch enrichment avoids per-conversation lookups
as the unified list grows.

13
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Group collaboration preserves sender identity
across every member's view.

14
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Bob's message appears with the correct author
and updates connected members through Socket.IO.

15
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
The Redis Adapter carries room events
across three Express replicas behind nginx.

16
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Realtime delivery is not limited to users
connected to the same backend process.

17
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:25,000
The Conversation Information Panel brings
shared context into one place.

18
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:30,000
It presents metadata, members, shared media,
files, and links.

19
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Each View All explorer owns its cursor
and infinite-scroll state.

20
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Freshness banners announce new resources
without disrupting the current snapshot.

21
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:45,000
The media lightbox keeps focused browsing
separate from the underlying conversation.

22
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:50,000
The panel becomes a shared-resource workspace,
not only a settings drawer.

23
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Calls use Socket.IO only for signaling.

24
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:00,000
After Bob accepts, WebRTC carries audio and video
directly between the peers.

25
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Media controls update during the call.

26
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:10,000
A MongoDB-gated finalizer protects the main
termination paths from conflicting call history.

27
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:15,000
KittaChat combines three Socket.IO replicas,
Redis coordination, RabbitMQ workers, and MongoDB.

28
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Its engineering story starts with cross-replica delivery
and retry-safe message persistence.

29
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:25,000
It also covers gated call finalization,
a scalable sidebar, and resilient background jobs.

30
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Tests, builds, source code, and design documents
are linked directly from the repository.
